&lt;li&gt;Lead and develop Sonatus’s global Talent Acquisition team across the US and Ireland.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive recruiting strategy and execution to support continued global growth across Engineering, AI, Product, Sales, and Operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a high-performance recruiting function focused on quality, speed, scalability, and operational excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI, automation, analytics, and evolving recruiting tools to improve recruiter efficiency, sourcing effectiveness, and candidate engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with business leaders and hiring managers to align hiring plans with company priorities and organizational growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continue strengthening recruiting processes, interviewer enablement, and hiring discipline across the company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and analyze recruiting metrics to identify trends, improve forecasting, and drive data-informed decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure a strong and consistent candidate experience across all stages of the hiring process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and influence employer branding and talent market positioning globally, particularly within competitive AI talent markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Step into hands-on recruiting for critical or senior-level roles when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continue optimizing external agency usage, ensuring partnerships are strategic, high quality, and cost-effective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
